Siviwe Anthony has re-joined the South African corporate team at Norton Rose Fulbright, where she was a candidate attorney (previously Deneys Reitz). She was admitted as an attorney in February 2007.Anthony specialises in mergers and acquisition and has advised local and international mining, industrial and manufacturing companies. She has a keen interest in structuring Black Economic Empowerment transactions, having acted in this regard for various entities such as Gold Fields and BHP Billion.Prior to re-joining Norton Rose Fulbright, Anthony ran her own legal practice and was previously a partner at ENSafrica. She has also practiced as a foreign associate at Kirkland &amp; Ellis LLP in New York. Anthony graduated from Rhodes University with a Bachelor of Commerce (Accounting &amp; Law) and a Bachelor of Laws.